elic <i>Donn</i> (see below). <i>Brown</i> (including in the senses below) is the fourth most frequent surname in the US. It is also very common among African Americans and Native Americans (see also 5 below).","Irish and Scottish: adopted for <b>Ó Duinn</b> (see   Dunn  ) or for any of the many Irish and Scottish Gaelic names containing the element <i>donn</i> ‘brown-haired’ (also meaning ‘chieftain’), for example   Donahue  .","Irish: phonetic Anglicization of <b>Mac an Bhreitheamhnaigh</b>; see   Breheny  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":32,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Browne V was born in August 1349, in Stamford, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, John Browne IV, was 34 and his mother, Alice Swinstead, was 28. He married Lady Katherine Stanford in 1368, in Stamford, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1410, in his hometown, at the age of 61, and was buried in Stamford, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"August 1349–1410":"august 1349–1410","1340–1398":"1340–1398","1349–1410":"1349–1410","1349–1400":"1349–1400","1350–1395":"1350–1395","1380–1442":"1380–1442","1400–Male":"1400–Surnud","1315–1398":"1315–1398","1321–1398":"1321–1398","8 September 1398":"8. september 1398","August 1349":"august 1349","1395":"1395","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1